Context: St. James Campus is located at 200 King Street East, Toronto ON M5A 3W8. The campus houses several centers and schools, including the Office of Research & Innovation. Prospective students can contact the English as Second Language center at (416) 415-5000, ext. 6339 or esl@georgebrown.ca for tours and inquiries. The Game Development program can be contacted at 341 King St. E., (416) 415-5000, ext. 3129 or game@georgebrown.ca. Campus tours showcase common areas like cafeteria, library, gym, student services, and other facilities. The main subway stop is King on the Yonge line. Parking lots can be found on parkopedia.ca. Other campus locations include 300 Adelaide Street East, Toronto ON M5A 1N1; 290 Adelaide Street East, Toronto ON M5A 1N1; 215 King Street East, Toronto ON M5A 1J9; and 230 Richmond Street East, Toronto ON M5A 1P4; as well as 193 King Street East, Toronto ON M5A 4M5 and 341 King Street East, Toronto ON M5A 1L1.
